<paragraph blockId="36.[2003,2589,715,1132]" pageId="36" pageNumber="443">
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="443" type="reference_group">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2003,2152,715,740]" pageId="36" pageNumber="443">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Hershkovitz, 1959" authorityName="Hershkovitz" authorityYear="1959" class="Mammalia" family="Cervidae" genus="Mazama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="36" pageNumber="443" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chunyi">Mazama chunyi Hershkovitz, 1959</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation box="[2083,2586,753,778]" pageId="36" pageNumber="443">
Cocapunco, Cordillera Real (
<collectingCountry box="[2475,2572,753,778]" name="Bolivia" pageId="36" pageNumber="443">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
).
</materialsCitation>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="443" type="discussion">
It has been confused for decades with the sympatric 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Winton" authorityYear="1896" box="[2147,2407,828,857]" class="Mammalia" family="Cervidae" genus="Pudu" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="36" pageNumber="443" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mephistophiles">Pudu mephistophiles</taxonomicName>
. Its scientific name, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hershkovitz" authorityYear="1959" box="[2106,2191,867,896]" class="Mammalia" family="Cervidae" genus="Mazama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="36" pageNumber="443" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chunyi">chunyi</taxonomicName>
, is from “chuni,” the Bolivian name for this species. Monotypic.
</subSubSection>
</paragraph>
<subSubSection box="[2003,2586,942,975]" pageId="36" pageNumber="443" type="distribution">
